Company Overview of Infrastructure Networks, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Infrastructure Networks, Inc. provides broadband wireless networks founded on 4G/LTE wireless technology. It offers subscription services; and CLOUDCORE, a service management platform that allows customers the ability to manage their services and subscriptions, as well as supports real time reporting of radio usage for specified intervals. The company also provides FAST L2 services that builds transparent Ethernet pipes over various combinations of public or private IP networks and can be configured to support carrier Ethernet/E-Line, carrier Ethernet/E-LAN, and carrier Ethernet/E-Tree. Further, it offers network overview and spectrum holdings services; and 4G LTE broadband wireless coverage...
Infrastructure Networks, Inc. provides broadband wireless networks founded on 4G/LTE wireless technology. It offers subscription services; and CLOUDCORE, a service management platform that allows customers the ability to manage their services and subscriptions, as well as supports real time reporting of radio usage for specified intervals. The company also provides FAST L2 services that builds transparent Ethernet pipes over various combinations of public or private IP networks and can be configured to support carrier Ethernet/E-Line, carrier Ethernet/E-LAN, and carrier Ethernet/E-Tree. Further, it offers network overview and spectrum holdings services; and 4G LTE broadband wireless coverage in Eagle Ford Shale, Permian Basin, and Texas Panhandle. It serves oil and natural gas exploration and production; water, oil, and natural gas pipelines and wells; coal and ore mines; railroads, roads, inland waterways, bridges, and tunnels; electric generation plants and distribution systems; and municipal traffic, utility, and public service systems. The company was founded in 2011 and is based in Houston, Texas.
