NETWORK OVERVIEW
The Infrastructure Networks network is built upon 4G LTE Cellular Technology, the globally adopted standard for wireless high-speed data.
4G LTE Capabilities:

Peak download rates up to 299.6 Mbit/s and Upload rates up to 75.4 Mbit/s (4x4 MIMO using 20 MHz Channels)
Low latency and connection set-up times, 50-80 ms round trip
Efficient modulation balance to support maximum downlink speeds and conserve power on the uplink data
Single cell coverage in open terrain of greater than 1,000 square miles. Small cells can be deployed to support areas of a few hundred yards
Native security through SIM Card (Subscriber Identity Module) authentication and robust symmetric key 128-bit encryption

 
